headline: Estée Lauder Suit Tests Walmart Marketplace Controls And Investor Sentiment
summary: Estée Lauder has sued Walmart, alleging that counterfeit versions of Aveda, Clinique, La Mer, Le Labo, and Tom Ford products were sold on Walmart's online marketplace. The lawsuit claims Walmart allowed third party sellers to offer fake items and did not adequately ensure listings were limited to authorized, authentic products. The case raises questions around Walmart's marketplace controls, its brand relationships, and potential legal and reputational risk linked to its e commerce...
